entries.meaning: A check; a relapse; a discouragement; a setback.
Whatever is thrown back in its course, such as water.
examples: Slackwater, or the backset caused by the overflow.

verbs.description: backset (third-person singular simple present backsets, present participle backsetting, simple past and past participle backset)

entries.meaning: (US, especially Western US) To plow again in the fall; said of prairie land broken up in the spring.
